title: A.o.M. I
author: ponz314
pages:
#- Archive of Ministers

2: Agriculture
4: Mining
6: Commerce
8: Construction
#- Agriculture

Food is a fundimental part of life, and it is logical to control it so that we do not die. Agriculture is the solution to this as we can generate food as we need it. With a minister of agriculture, food will not be in shortage, but if it is, 
#- it will evenly spread out to the people so that they will not starve.
#- Mining

The riches of the earth have been desired since the dawn of minecraft. Stone and iron are needed to build society to the point in which it can get gold, diamonds, and redstone. A minister of mining can ensure that these riches are 
#- used in the correct way and places, so that we do not waste them on trivial things.
#- Commerce

Ever since two people wanted what the other had, there has been trade. Trade lead to banking, economics, and commerce. Commerce is the collective sum of all trades, savings, and debt, into one, simple unit. A minster of commerce would 
#- regulate trade, establish a currency, deal with banking issues, and settle contract disputes. This would keep order in a choatic order of material goods.
#- Construction

Once we had the materials to build with and the food to keep us alive, we built great things. Libraries, quaries, factories, banks, religous center, monuments, etc. However, some things are a waste of material. A minister of 
#- construction would dictate design, placement, and usage of materials to build things in a efficent, but beautiful, manner.
#- 